      "content": "i get what u mean, but u seem pretty set on the idea that the safety net is the main culprit. what about the argument that these programs actually help people find *better* jobs by providing a floor, instead of just making them lazy? it seems like some economists argue that the \"dependency\" thing is more of a political talking point than an actual reality. why do u think one side of that debate is more valid than the other?",
